<blockquote>''Join the fight between Prisoners and Guards in this VR prisonǃ Plot your escape with friends or keep the prisoners in lineǃ''</blockquote>


'''Prison Escape''' is a cross-platform player-versus-player [[Special:MyLanguage/Category:Game worlds|game world]] that can be played with up to 32 players.

==Gameplay==
Players spawn inside a prison, divided into two roles - prisoners and guards. Their objective is to led their team to victory either by eliminating everyone from the opposite team, or completing role specific goals - escaping the facility as a prisoner or preventing any escapees until the time runs out as a guard. The game area is filled with items, locations and special events players can utilize to their advantage, e.g. weapons, vents, causing a fire or blackouts. Additionally players can earn points by collecting money, winning or eliminations, and spend them on opening crates that drop special items and weapons. While guards spawn with guns immediately available to them and being able to access every area, the prisoner gameplay is more nuanced and opportunistic.
== Roles==
=== Prisoner===
Prisoners start as innocent and can't be attacked by guards until they do a prohibited action that discretely marks them temporarily as suspicious or permanently as wanted, e.g. picking up weapons or entering restricted areas. Their goal is to escape the facility or eliminate all guards.
====Win conditions====

*A prisoner escapes.
*All guards eliminated.

====States====
