===Guard===
====Win conditions====  

* Time runs out.
*All prisoners eliminated.

==Game settings==
*Prisoner ratio.
*Time limit.   
**4 to 8 minutes or unlimited.

==Points==
Players collect points, which can be spend on opening crates that drop unique items and weapons.

Points can be earned through:

*Collecting money piles.
*Winning.
*Eliminations.
*Collecting rewards for eliminating most wanted players.
*Shooting CCTV cameras as a prisoner.
Patreon supporters have access to an option to double the points that they earn.

==Player stats ==

===Health===
'''Taking damage'''

Players can take damage by being attacked by other players using weapons. Additionally a guard will receive damage when attacking an innocent prisoner and a prisoner loses HP after sticking a '''fork''' into a '''power outlet''' causing a '''blackout'''.

'''Healing'''

Health will start to slowly restore itself after a while. Additionally the beds in the Infirmary can heal too.

===Armor===
Armor acts as extra health. It can only be received by collecting a '''bulletproof vest''' from a crate.

===Speed===
Player speed can be sometimes be altered throughout the gameplay. Collecting an '''energy drink''' from a crate will permanently increase player's speed and walking through the gas from a '''gas grenade''' will slow them down. Sticking a '''fork''' into a '''power outlet''' causing a '''blackout''' or being hit with a '''stun baton''' causes a temporary stun.

